SIMPLE: skid_road
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skid road
<hw>Skid road</hw>. <fld>(Logging)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A road along
which logs are dragged to the skidway or landing; -- called also
<altname>travois road</altname> <it>or</it> <altname>travoy
road</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A road having partly sunken
transverse logs (called <xex>skids</xex>) at intervals of about five
feet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skied</ent>⟦br⟧
